title: Male Factor Infertility
case:
32M, SA: Volume 2.5mL, concentration 8M/mL, motility 25% progressive, morphology 2% normal. Partner 30F, normal reserve. TTC 2 years.

Q: Diagnosis, investigations, and treatment options?
full_response:
Donor insemination. Explanation: 32-year-old man with no medical problems or issues related to sexual activity has a poor sperm analysis (SA). The husband is not the cause of infertility in this couple. Donor insemination would be appropriate for this couple.
